observations.recommendation:
We recommended that the Municipal Mayor require the:
a. Special Disbursing Officer for the Confidential Fund to provide clear statement of the duration of implementation of the projects for implementation and submit the transmittal letter duly acknowledged/received by the Intelligence and Confidential Funds Audit Unit to be submitted by the Special Disbursing Officer;
b. Municipal Accountant to record the liquidation of cash advance based on the transmittal letter duly acknowledged/received by the Intelligence and Confidential Funds Audit Unit;
c. Municipal Accountant to stop processing and granting new cash advance for Confidential Expenses if the previous cash advances were not yet liquidated and submitted by the Special Disbursing Officer to Intelligence and Confidential Funds Audit Unit; and
d. Municipal Accountant to ensure that all cash advances for confidential expenses were submitted to the Audit Team within seven (7) days from the date of release of check; and
e. Special Disbursing Officer to ensure that all cash advances for Confidential Expenses will be liquidated as of year-end.

We recommended that the Municipal Mayor require the Municipal Accountant and the OIC, Human Resource and Management Officer to:
a) Regularly reconcile employees’ records at GSIS, PhilHealth and PAG-IBIG to identify the affected employees on the unremitted balances and immediately remit the amounts due to these agencies;
b) Identify the cause/s of the under remittance for some accounts and make the proper adjustments;
c) Effect payroll deduction on loan amortization of employees who availed loan with GSIS and remit the same pursuant to Section 14.2, Rule III of the Implementing Rules and Regulations of Government Service Insurance Act of 1997 or R.A. 8291 to avoid incurrence of unnecessary financial expenses in the form of imposed penalties; and
d) Determine remittances which exceeded the amount deducted from payroll and make liable the concerned municipal employee who prepared and approved the schedule of remittances.
